<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Swenson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 260</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to forward, under
                            separate cover, for the files of the Department, copies of public
                            documents relating to the ratification of the treaty for the cession of
                            the Danish West Indies to the United States.<note n="8" xml:id="d730fn25">Not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>These documents embrace the diplomatic correspondence submitted to the
                            Rigsdag by the Danish Foreign Office; the committee reports <pb facs="0706" n="540" xml:id="pg_540"/> and resolutions of the
                            Rigsdag; and verbatim reports of the debates in the two houses on the
                            question of ratification.</p>
                        <p>I will thank you to favor this office with similar documents published by
                            the Government of the United States.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Laurits S. Swenson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>